-5 Kitchen space: a space with required light and ventilation according to relevant standards, equipped with facilities and appliances for storing food, preparation, cooking, and serving. In some cases, utensils needed for eating are also placed in this space.
Kitchens are classified architecturally into three types:
A) Independent kitchen, separated from other spaces by doors and other elements;
B) Open kitchen, where the kitchen space is connected to other spaces without doors or architectural separators;
